<title>USA: Electroscope names new CEO/President.</title>
<headline>Electroscope names new CEO/President.</headline>
<dateline>BOULDER, Colo. 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Electroscope Inc said Thursday it has named Patrick Crane chief executive and president.</p>
<p>Crane succeeds Roger Odell, who has been named chairman.</p>
<p>Most recently, Crane was vice president of research and development at Ohmeda Medical Systems, a division of British Oxygen Corp.</p>
<p>Electroscope designs and manufactures a patented array of shielded monopolar accessories.</p>
